New York, USA ~ A MAN attacked a Hanukkah celebration at a rabbi’s home, stabbing and wounding five people before fleeing in a vehicle. Police said the stabbings happened at about 10pm on Saturday in Monsey, one of several Hudson Valley towns that have seen an increase in the number of Hasidic Jews in recent years. Saturday was the seventh night of Hanukkah.  The Orthodox Jewish Public Affairs Council for the Hudson Valley region confirmed the stabbings. Several state and local officials described the location as a synagogue. The rabbi’s home is next door to a synagogue. Ramapo Police Chief Brad Weide said the five people were taken to hospitals for treatment. He said hours later police had located a vehicle and a possible suspect. – NEWS24